The evidence with the title 'Extreme poverty is falling: how is poverty changing for higher ... ' says Mar 5, 2018  ... Today , about 10% of the world population lives in extreme poverty, while in 1990 the corresponding figure was about 37 % . ... Switch to the ' relative ' view , you see that poverty rates have been going down for all of the included poverty lines. ... Today less than 12 % of the population live below this threshold . 
